HEADWORD: Paganism
<hw>Pa"gan*ism</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>paganismus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>paganisme</ets>. See <er>Pagan</er>,
and cf. <er>Painim</er>.]</ety> <def>The state of being pagan; pagan
characteristics; esp., the worship of idols or false gods, or the system
of religious opinions and worship maintained by pagans;
heathenism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

